<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-12-07T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-12-07T06:00:00-05:00" n="361" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d361">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77 Chinese Eastern/635:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Yugoslavia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">George</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Belgrade</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-12-07T12:00:00+01:00">December 7,
                                1929—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 6:30 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>23. Department’s circular of December 1, 4 p.m. I am orally informed by
                            Foreign Office, Yugoslav Minister at Washington telegraphically
                            instructed to accomplish full adherence to proposals regarding Manchuria
                            and that declaration will be published in Belgrade.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">George</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>